Now I understand the core issue. The OCI spec has two separate sections:
1. `linux.resources.devices` - cgroup device rules (allow/deny entries)
2. `linux.devices` - devices to make available in the container (should be implicitly allowed)

When `linux.resources.devices` has a deny-all rule `[{"allow": false, "access": "rwm"}]` and `linux.devices` has a specific device like `/dev/net/tun`, crun's eBPF program only processes the deny-all rule but doesn't add allow rules for the devices in `linux.devices`. The fix needs to add allow rules for devices listed in `linux.devices` to the eBPF program.

